The accompanying drawings, which are included to provide a further understanding of the present invention and are incorporated in and constitute a part of this application, illustrate embodiment(s) of the present invention and together with the description serve to explain the principle of the present invention. In the drawings:
FIG. 1 is a schematic view showing a state in which a user opens a door of a general oven;
FIG. 2 is a schematic view showing a chamber of a conventional oven;
FIG. 3 is a schematic view showing a rack removed from another conventional oven;
FIG. 4 is a schematic view showing a use state of an oven according to one embodiment of the present invention;
FIG. 5 is a bottom perspective view showing a retracted state of an operating member included in a rack assembly according to one embodiment of the present invention;
FIG. 6 is a bottom perspective view showing a pulled state of the operating member in the rack assembly shown in FIG. 5;
FIG. 7 is a top perspective view showing a retracted state of the operating member in the rack assembly shown in FIG. 5;
FIG. 8 is a bottom perspective view showing the rack assembly shown in FIG. 5, to which a shock-absorbing member is added; and
FIG. 9 is a bottom perspective view showing the rack assembly shown in FIG. 5, to which a damper is added.

ol.li:
1. An oven 100 comprising:
a cabinet 200 having a chamber 250 configured to receive a cooking object C therein;
a door 300 configured to open or close the cabinet 200;
a rack assembly 400 including an operating member 500 configured to support the cooking object C seated thereon and to be removable outward from the interior of the chamber 250, and a support member 600 fixed inside the chamber 250 to support the operating member 500 disposed thereon; and
a spring device 700 including a first fixing piece 720 located at the operating member 500, a second fixing piece 730 located at the support member 600, and an elastic member 710 having one side connected to the first fixing piece 720 and the other side connected to the second fixing piece 730, the elastic member 710 being located in a vertical gap between the operating member 500 and the support member 600 and being elastically restored by a distance between the first fixing piece 720 and the second fixing piece 730 to remove the operating member 500 from the chamber 250.

20. An oven 100 comprising:
a cabinet 200 having a chamber 250 configured to receive a cooking object C therein;
a door 300 configured to open or close the cabinet 200;
a rack assembly 400 including an operating member 500 configured to support the cooking object C seated thereon and to be removable outward from the interior of the chamber 250, and a support member 600 fixed inside the chamber 250 to support the operating member 500 disposed thereon; and
a spring device 700 including a first fixing piece 720 located at an operating member bracket 510 of the operating member 500, a second fixing piece 730 located at a support member frame 630 of the support member 600, and an elastic member 710 having one side connected to the first fixing piece 720 and the other side connected to the second fixing piece 730, the elastic member 710 being elastically restored by a distance between the first fixing piece 720 and the second fixing piece 730 to remove the operating member 500 from the chamber 250.

32. An oven 100 comprising:
a cabinet 200 having a chamber 250 configured to receive a cooking object C therein;
a door 300 configured to open or close the cabinet 200;
a rack support member including a pair of support member brackets 610, a support member rail 620 coupled to each of the support member brackets 610, and a support member frame connecting both the support member brackets 610 to each other;
a rack operating member including a pair of operating member brackets 510, an operating member rail 520 coupled to each of the operating member brackets 510, the operating member rail 520 being connected to the support member rail 620, and an operating member frame 500 connecting both the operating member brackets 510 to each other; and
a spring device 700 configured to remove the operating member 500 from the chamber 250 by being elastically restored as the door 300 is opened, and to introduce the operating member 500 into the chamber 250 by being elastically deformed as the door 300 is closed.

claim.claim-text:
An oven (100) comprising:
a cabinet (200) having a chamber (250) configured to receive a cooking object (C) therein;
a door (300) configured to open or close the cabinet (200);
a rack assembly (400) including an operating member (500) configured to support the cooking object (C) seated thereon and to be removable outward from the interior of the chamber (250), and a support member (600) fixed inside the chamber (250) to support the operating member (500) disposed thereon; and
a spring device (700) including a first fixing piece (720) located at the operating member (500), a second fixing piece (730) located at the support member (600), and an elastic member (710) having one side connected to the first fixing piece (720) and the other side connected to the second fixing piece (730), the elastic member (710) being elastically restored by a distance between the first fixing piece (720) and the second fixing piece (730) to remove the operating member (500) from the chamber (250).
